np.random.shuffle(samples)  # Shuffle the samples to mix different categories

    energy = np.random.uniform(*np.quantile(energy, [0.15, 0.85]))  # Adjusted based on some hypothetical constraints for demonstration purposes
    spot_size = round(spot_size, decimals=3)
    intensity = round(intensity * np.random.uniform(-np.quantile(energy*0.1), decimals=4)  # Simplified; actual adjustment would consider covariance with energy more thoroughly
    power = round(power + np.random.normal(0, 0.5) * (len(energy)/200)  # Assuming some hypothetical constraints for demonstration purposes
    cutoff_energy = round(cutoff_energy, decimals=1)
    
    # Append the adjusted data point to our dataset
